- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on detecting communities in complex networks, especially social networks.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper proposes an algorithm to improve the Label Propagation Algorithm, which is a common algorithm used in software engineering for community detection.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper discusses various algorithms for community detection and proposes a new algorithm based on edge betweenness metric.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper uses a metric to improve the Label Propagation Algorithm, which is a machine learning algorithm.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the scalability of the proposed algorithm, which is related to system and control.
